		<h3>Daily Fiction</h3>
		<h1>“Wild Light”</h1>
		<h2>By Sarah Gerkensmeyer</h2>
		<div class="img-excerpt-container">
			<div class="img-container"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/MQR-Special-Edition-spring-2026-design-13.jpg" alt="“Wild Light”"></div>
			<div class="excerpt-container"><div class="excerpt"><em>The following is from Sarah Gerkensmeyer’s story from the new issue of </em>MRQ<em>. Gerkensmeyer’s story collection, </em>What You Are Now Enjoying<em>, was selected by Stewart O’Nan as winner of the Autumn House Press Fiction Prize. Her stories and poetry have appeared in </em>American Short Fiction, Guernica, The Massachusetts Review, The Normal School, Catapult, Nimrod, Copper Nickel, PANK, Hayden’s Ferry Review,<em> and elsewhere.</em></div></div>
